ions, full morpheme-by-morpheme glosses, and a glossary of specialized terminology, this book is certain to be both an invaluable resource for scholars and a tool for those who want to ensure that Lushootseed is used by generations to come.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aPuget Sound Salish IndiansvFolklore. 0aPuget Sound Salish languagesvTextbooks for foreign speakersxEnglish. 0aPuget Sound Salish languagesvTexts. 0aPuget Sound Salish languagesxRevival. 0aTaleszWashington (State). 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh1 aHess, Thom, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aJames, Agnes Jules, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKrise, Elizabeth Charles, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLamont, Martha Williams, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSam, Edward, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2014z978311127407208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2014z978311127709708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of British Columbia Complete eBook-Package 2014z978311141999240uhttps://doi.org/10.59962/978077482357940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780774823579423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780774823579/original  a978-3-11-127407-2  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2014b2014  a978-3-11-127709-7  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2014b2014  a978-3-11-141999-2  University of British Columbia Complete eBook-Package 2014b2014  aGBV-deGruyter-alles